OL,3,CBoy, 14, seriously injured in attack
OL,4,Cby two escaped dogs
OL,6,FDevizes Neighbourhood Inspector Simon
OL,7,FGarrett said: "We appreciate how
OL,8,Fhorrendous and distressing this
OL,9,Fincident must have been for the
OL,10,Fvictim, his family and those who
OL,11,Fwitnessed it and we are taking it very
OL,12,Fseriously.
OL,14,F"The two dogs involved have been
OL,15,Fseized and taken to secure kennels and
OL,16,Ftheir owner has been identified.
OL,18,F"Enquiries are ongoing to understand
OL,19,Fthe full circumstances of the incident.
